{"type":"message","id":"ea208feb","parentId":"d2c3924d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T03:08:52.591Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `import` endpoint is wrong. Let me check the correct Feishu API for image upload. The correct endpoint for uploading images to send as messages is:\n\n`POST https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/images` with `image_type=message`\n\nBut I used `/images/import` which is wrong. Let me try the correct one. Wait, I used the correct one in the first script (`https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/images`) and got 234001. \n\nThe error 234001 \"Invalid request param\" suggests the file format might be wrong, or the image is too large, or wrong content type. \n\nThe original endpoint was correct, so the 234001 error might mean the bot lacks the `im:message` permission. Let me try uploading to Feishu Drive instead and then send the file key as an attachment message.\n\nActually, I could send a post message with the image URL embedded using the image key, but that requires the user to be able to access the URL. The image might not be publicly accessible since it's just a local file. Let me try sending images as base64 encoded data in the message content instead.\n\nWait, Feishu doesn't support sending images as base64 directly in text messages. Let me think about this differently - the issue is likely that the bot token doesn't have `im:message:send_as_app` permission. Looking at the successful text message responses and the image upload error, it seems the token works for text but fails for image uploads.\n\nMaybe I should try the correct endpoint for image uploads - `POST /open-apis/im/v1/images` with the image type parameter, and make sure the image field name is correct.\n\nThe 234001 error with \"Invalid request param\" is puzzling though. Let me consider whether the bot actually has image upload permissions, or if there's a domain whitelist issue preventing the upload.\n\nI think the best path forward