{"type":"message","id":"6788d17d","parentId":"718c42e8","timestamp":"2026-04-12T03:09:27.563Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu app scopes tool doesn't work because the \"default\" account isn't configured. Let me check the correct account name. From the config, there's \"main\" and \"default\". The \"main\" account has the appId/appSecret configured. Maybe I need to specify the account. But actually the tool might use the \"default\" account. Let me try a different approach.\n\nThe issue is that the image upload API (`/im/v1/images`) returns code 234001 \"Invalid request param\". This might be because:\n1. The bot doesn't have `im:message` or `im:message:send_as_bot` permission\n2. The image_type parameter is wrong\n3. The file field name is wrong\n\n\n4. I need to explore the correct API endpoint and parameters for uploading images through the bot\n\nLet me try a different approach using the Feishu SDK or a simpler image upload method. I think the issue might be that I'm using the wrong endpoint or the bot lacks the necessary permissions to upload images.\n\nLooking at the error code 234001 \"Invalid request param\" from the `/im/v1/images` endpoint, this typically indicates either a parameter format problem or missing permissions. I should try adjusting the `image_type` parameter value, or switch to the `import_image` endpoint instead.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the bot needs specific image permissions configured in the developer console - `im:message:send_as_bot` for sending images and `im:message` for general messaging access. Since `send_flights.py` successfully sent text messages, the issue is specifically with the image upload endpoint.\n\nLet me try a different approach - I could upload the image to a file service first and send it as a URL, or explore other Feishu image APIs. But honestly, since the text messages are already going through successfully, the images might not be the priority here. Let me verify what the cron job actually needs by looking at the delivery requirements again.\n\nThe task explicitly asks for both content and cover images in each message, so images do matter. Let me try uploading to Feishu's drive API instead to get an image key, since the message API can accept image keys directly. Or I could use the `upload_file` endpoint which supports image uploads.\n\nActually, I'm going in circles here. The simplest path forward is to bundle the images as attachments in the existing `send_flights.py` script - Feishu's message API does support sending images as files through multipart form data, so let me just try that approach rather than trying to get image keys from separate upload endpoints."},{"type":"text","text":"文字5条已成功发送。图片上传遇到权限问题（234001）。尝试用 multipart 方式发送图片消息：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pwryfifte9z7_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\send_images2.py","content":"import requests, json, os, sys\n\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\nsys.stderr.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\napp_id = 'cli_a934245330789ccf'\nlocations = [r'C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\openclaw.env', r'C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\feishu.env']\napp_secret = ''\nfor p in locations:\n    if os.path.exists(p):\n        for line in open(p, encoding='utf-8').read().splitlines():\n            if 'FEISHU_APP_SECRET' in line:\n                app_secret = line.split('=', 1)[1].strip().strip('\"\\'')\n                break\n    if app_secret:\n        break\nif not app_secret:\n    app_secret = os.environ.get('FEISHU_APP_SECRET', '')\n\ntoken_url = 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal'\nr = requests.post(token_url, json={'app_id': app_id, 'app_secret': app_secret}, timeout=10)\ntoken = r.json().get('tenant_access_token', '')\n\nuser_id = 'ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b'\nmsg_url = 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages?receive_id_type=open_id'\n\nresults = []\nfor i in range(1, 6):\n    img_path = os.path.join(r'C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\uploads', f'xhs_push_{i}.jpg')\n    \n    if os.path.exists(img_path):\n        with open(img_path, 'rb') as f:\n            img_data = f.read()\n        \n        # 构造 multipart/form-data 发送图片消息\n        import uuid\n        boundary = uuid.uuid4().hex\n        \n        # JSON part\n        json_part = json.dumps({\n            'receive_id': user_id,\n            'msg_type': 'image',\n            'content': json.dumps({'image_key': f'img_{i}'})\n        })\n        \n        body = (\n            f'--{boundary}\\r\\n'\n            f'Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"request\"\\r\\n'\n            f'Content-Type: application/json\\r\\n\\r\\n'\n            f'{json_part}\\r\\n'\n            f'--{boundary}\\r\\n'\n            f'Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"image\"; filename=\"xhs_push_{i}.jpg\"\\r\\n'\n            f'Content-Type: image/jpeg\\r\\n\\r\\n'\n        ).encode('utf-8') + img_data + f'\\r\\n--{boundary}--'.encode('utf-8')\n        \n        headers = {\n            'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}',\n            'Content-Type': f'multipart/form-data; boundary={boundary}'\n        }\n        \n        msg_r = requests.post(msg_url, headers=headers, data=body, timeout=30)\n        print(f'[{i}] status={msg_r.status_code}')\n        try:\n            res = msg_r.json()\n            print(f'  code={res.get(\"code\")}')\n            if res.get('code') == 0:\n                results.append(f'[{i}] OK')\n            else:\n                print(f'  error: {res}')\n        except:\n            print(f'  raw: {msg_r.text[:200]}')\n\nprint(f'\\n成功: {len(results)}/5')\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775963332597}}
